# Unit 6 Lessons > Days 6-7

## Concepts Covered

Get to know the “brain” of the robot (NXT Brick), input/output devices, use built-in NXT Brick programs.

## Lesson Overview

In this lesson you’ll be going over the brain of the robot, as well as the base, lights, motors, and three wheels (NXT User Guide 9-12).  Review input ports number 1-4, output ports A-C, the buttons, the lines in the right side (speaker), and point out the rechargeable battery. Have them explore what happens when they press the orange button and walk them through what they see.  Ask guiding questions for them to explore the input and output devices, view menu, motor, try me menu, program menu p 15-16, 22-45).
 
